MacVlan Networks

Issue "ifconfig" and observer only docker0 and ens32 (if its ubuntu) and lo adapters showing up. 

Then issue the following command to create a macvlan 
docker network create -d macvlan -o parent=ens32 --subnet 192.168.0.0/24 --gateway 192.168.0.1 --ip-range 192.168.0.192/27 --aux-address 'host=192.168.0.223' my_macnet

-d --> driver
-o --> options
--subnet --> your network address range
--gateway --> your network gateway
--ip-range --> exclude specific ip's from subnet range to use for container allocation
--aux-address --> reserved for new virtual interface that we are going to create to macvlan work
host --> mac0 virtual interface that we are going to create and to assign its ip

Add bonding between mac0 (virtual interface) and docker hosts main interface
ip link add mac0 link ens32 type macvlan mode bridge

Assign ip address to mac0 (virtual interface)
ip addr add 192.168.0.223/32 dev mac0

Bring mac0 up
ifconfig mac0 up

Check if its showing up
ifconfig

Add a route to let docker-host how to communicate with containers directly as they are existing side by side
ip route add 192.168.0.192/27 dev mac0

NOTE: change your ip's according to your network

Finally, create a container on macvlan
docker run -dit --name srv01 --network=my_macnet centos 
docker inspect srv01 (get ip of the container)
ping that container ip from docker host directly and vice versa

