To create a Docker Volume use the command: 
docker volume create testvol1

To verify you have successfully created a Docker volume, prompt Docker to list all available volumes with:
docker volume ls

To see more information about a Docker volume, use the inspect command: 
docker volume inspect testvol1

To mount a data volume to a container add the --mount flag to the docker run command. It adds the volume to the specified container, where it stores the data produced inside the virtual environment. 
docker run -it --name=srv02 --mount source=testvol1,destination=/data centos

create some files on docker container in the newly attached volume
docker exec -it srv01 /bin/bash
cd /data
touch file.txt
vi file.txt
type some random data in the file.....
press escape on keyboard after typing the data
press :
type wq and then ENTER to save the file.

Verify the same data reflecting on host volume
navigate to actual path of the volume (you can retrieve it from docker volume inspect testvol1 ex: /var/....)
cd to that directory
issue ls command to list of files
cat file.txt to see the data that we added from the container.  
